The modified code still adheres to the original logic of counting pairs (A, B) where the first digit of A equals the last digit of B and vice versa. The input types and operations are also validated, ensuring type safety.

The overall time complexity has been improved from O(N^2) to O(N) for the frequency count and then O(1) for calculating the answer using precomputed values, making the solution much more efficient, especially for larger values of N.

This optimized version is suitable for competitive programming and large input sizes, thanks to its reduced complexity and improved performance characteristics.

